### [3 John Chapter 1](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#001.md)

[3 John](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">jo3 1:0</span></span>

Overview

[Jo3 1:1](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#001.md), He commends Gaius for his
piety, [Jo3 1:5](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#005.md), and hospitality, [Jo3
1:7](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#007.md), to true preachers; [Jo3
1:9](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#009.md), complaining of the unkind dealing
of ambitious Diotrephes on the contrary side; [Jo3
1:11](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#011.md), whose evil example is not to be
followed; [Jo3 1:12](../../../bib/kjv/jo3001.htm#012.md), and gives special
testimony to the good report of Demetrius.

